<DOC><DOCNO> ZF310-630-859 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 630 859.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Design  April 11 1991 v39 n7 p65(8).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>High-resolution ADCs up dynamic range in more applications.andO;(analog-to-digital converters) (includes ADC buyer's guide)(buyers guide)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Goodenough, Frank.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Military radar applications and sensing seismic signalapplications are two examples of analog-to-digital converter (ADC)applications which have encouraged programmers to enhance theperformance levels of ADCs.andP;  Areas which have been improvedinclude ADC packaging, processing and circuit design.andP;  Advancesare being made in high-resolution ADC technology in the area ofmonolithic ADCs.andP;  Currently, four architectures are being used fordevelopment: delta-sigma architecture, multipass architecture,integrating architecture and successive-approximation-registerarchitecture.andP;  Experts believe that the market will be led byconverters which are focused on connecting a type of sensor orsignal, overtaking the market for general-purpose converters.andO;Analysts also forecast that more low-cost converters will bedeveloped which are dedicated to particular applications.andP;  Adiscussion of specific high-resolution ADC products is included.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     DirectoriesAnalog-to-digital convertersPerformance ImprovementDigital CommunicationsCommunications EquipmentCircuit DesignNew TechniqueHardware SelectionCommunications Circuits.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   High-resolution analog-to-digital converter performance gamut.andO;(graph)Two novel ADC architectures. (graph)New and old applications for ADCs. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>